Make mytetra build under Qt6.

Upstream claims Qt6 support via `greaterThan(QT_MAJOR_VERSION, 4)` in
app.pro, but many source files still use APIs removed in Qt6 or rely on
version-guarded blocks that only cover Qt4/Qt5. Fixes:

* CssHelper.cpp, ScreenHelper.cpp: the local `dpi`/`size` variables were
  only declared inside `QT_VERSION < 0x060000` blocks. Extend to Qt6.

* SortHelper.h, AppConfig.h: `class QStringList;` — QStringList is a
  `using`-alias in Qt6, forward-declaring it as a class fails. Replace
  with `#include <QStringList>`.

* LinkHelper.cpp, Editor.cpp, MetaEditor.cpp, FindScreen.cpp, Record.cpp,
  ImageFormatter.cpp, TypefaceFormatter.cpp: `QRegExp` is unavailable in
  QString overloads (contains/split/replace) in Qt6 even with Qt5Compat.
  Switch call sites and declarations to `QRegularExpression`.

* MetaEditor.cpp, FindScreen.cpp: `QString::SkipEmptyParts` →
  `Qt::SkipEmptyParts` (old spelling removed in Qt6).

* InfoFieldEnter.cpp, MetaEditor.cpp, RecordInfoFieldsEditor.cpp,
  AddNewRecord.cpp, EditorMathExpressionDialog.cpp: `QLayout::setMargin(n)`
  removed in Qt6; use `setContentsMargins(n, n, n, n)`.

* EditorConfig.cpp, DatabasesManagementModel.cpp, KnownBasesConfig.cpp,
  DataBaseConfig.cpp, AppConfigUpdater.cpp, AppConfig.cpp:
  `QSettings::setIniCodec()` removed in Qt6 (UTF-8 is now the default).
  Guard with a version check so Qt5 behavior is preserved.

* Editor.cpp, Record.cpp, RecordTableData.cpp, KnowTreeModel.cpp,
  RecordTablePrint.cpp: `QTextStream::setCodec()` / `QXmlStreamWriter::
  setCodec()` removed in Qt6. Guard likewise.

* RecordTableModel.cpp, ActionLogModel.cpp: `Qt::SystemLocaleDate` removed
  in Qt6. Use `QLocale::system().toString()` which produces the same
  formatted output.

* MainWindow.cpp: `QDesktopWidget` header removed in Qt6, and
  `QApplication::desktop()->physicalDpi{X,Y}()` replaced by
  `QGuiApplication::primaryScreen()->physicalDotsPerInch{X,Y}()`.

* PrintPreview.cpp: `QPrinter::pageRect()` requires a Unit argument in
  Qt6; pass `QPrinter::Point` to preserve the previous behavior.

* Editor.cpp: `QDateTime::toTime_t()` → `toSecsSinceEpoch()`;
  `QTextDocument::toHtml("UTF-8")` → `toHtml()` (encoding argument
  removed, output is always UTF-8).

* EditorFindDialog.cpp: `QTextDocument::FindFlags flags=0` fails in Qt6
  because the int→FindFlag conversion is rejected; default-construct
  instead.

* CommandRunner.h: `class QTextCodec;` forward decl fails with Qt5Compat
  providing the definition; use a full `#include <QTextCodec>` instead.


* TrashMonitoring.cpp, ActionLogger.cpp: additional toTime_t() sites
  ported to toSecsSinceEpoch().

* EditorTextArea.cpp, EditorToolBarAssistant.cpp, IndentSlider.cpp:
  QPainter::HighQualityAntialiasing removed in Qt6; use Antialiasing.

* RecordTablePrint.cpp: additional toHtml("UTF-8") site.

* Record.cpp, TypefaceFormatter.cpp: port QRegExp loops that use
  indexIn/cap/matchedLength to QRegularExpressionMatchIterator.
  Drop .setMinimal(true) and pass InvertedGreedinessOption at
  construction instead.

* TypefaceFormatter.cpp: QDomDocument::setContent returns ParseResult
  in Qt6; cast to bool explicitly.

* AttachTableController.cpp: QFileDialog::DirectoryOnly -> Directory.

* Downloader.h: another class QStringList; forward decl.

* ShortcutManager.cpp, GlobalParameters.cpp: additional setIniCodec
  sites, guarded with #if QT_VERSION < 0x060000.

* ActionLogModel.cpp: QDateTime::fromTime_t -> fromSecsSinceEpoch.

* ClipboardBranch.cpp: QMap::unite() removed in Qt6; use insert(map).

* EditorMathExpressionDialog.cpp: QLabel::pixmap() returns a QPixmap
  by value in Qt6 (not a const QPixmap *); update nullptr check and
  pointer-style member accesses accordingly.

